(# Weapon Spear Homing \\(Code-First, Math Explained\\)) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(This guide explains the homing calculations used by `WeaponSpear` in this project.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## 1\\) Target Direction) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Code pattern:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(```csharp) Tj
T*
(Vector2 desiredDirection = \\(Vector2\\)\\(target.transform.position - transform.position\\);) Tj
T*
(desiredDirection.Normalize\\(\\);) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Math meaning:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- `targetPos - projectilePos` gives a vector that points from spear to enemy.) Tj
T*
(- Normalizing turns it into unit length \\(magnitude = 1\\), so direction is separated from speed.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Formula:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(`d = \\(p_target - p_projectile\\) / |p_target - p_projectile|`) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Why this matters:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- You can use the same direction for velocity and rotation, then apply speed independently.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## 2\\) Nearest Target Selection) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Code pattern:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(```csharp) Tj
T*
(float distanceSqr = \\(\\(Vector2\\)enemy.transform.position - currentPosition\\).sqrMagnitude;) Tj
T*
(if \\(distanceSqr < closestDistanceSqr\\)) Tj
T*
({) Tj
T*
(    closestDistanceSqr = distanceSqr;) Tj
T*
(    target = enemy;) Tj
T*
(}) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Math meaning:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- Euclidean distance is `sqrt\\(dx^2 + dy^2\\)`.) Tj
T*
(- For comparison only, square root is unnecessary.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Formula:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(`dist2 = dx^2 + dy^2`) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Why use squared distance:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- Faster and stable for frequent checks in physics updates.) Tj
T*
(- Ordering is identical to actual distance because sqrt is monotonic.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## 3\\) Snap Steering vs Smooth Steering) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(### Snap \\(used after pierce retarget\\)) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
