( ) Tj
T*
(Code idea:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(```csharp) Tj
T*
(nextDirection = desiredDirection;) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- Immediately points to the selected target.) Tj
T*
(- Good when you want sharp retarget behavior on impact.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(### Smooth Turn-Rate Steering \\(continuous homing\\)) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Code pattern:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(```csharp) Tj
T*
(float turnRadians = Mathf.Deg2Rad * homingTurnSpeedDegrees * deltaTime;) Tj
T*
(Vector2 nextDirection = Vector3.RotateTowards\\(currentDirection, desiredDirection, turnRadians, 0f\\);) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Math meaning:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- You cap angular change each tick.) Tj
T*
(- Let `omega` be max angular speed \\(rad/s\\), `dt` be timestep.) Tj
T*
(- Max angle step this tick: `theta_max = omega * dt`.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(In code:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- `homingTurnSpeedDegrees` is deg/s.) Tj
T*
(- `Mathf.Deg2Rad * homingTurnSpeedDegrees` converts to rad/s.) Tj
T*
(- Multiply by `deltaTime` to get allowed radians this frame.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Why this matters:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- Produces curved trajectories instead of instant snapping every frame.) Tj
T*
(- Gives a tunable feel: low value = wide arcs, high value = aggressive turning.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(## 4\\) Velocity Update) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Code pattern:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(```csharp) Tj
T*
(_weaponRb.linearVelocity = nextDirection * _currentSpeed;) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Math meaning:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- Velocity vector is direction multiplied by scalar speed.) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Formula:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(`v = d * s`) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(Where:) Tj
T*
( ) Tj
T*
(- `d` is unit direction.) Tj
T*
(- `s` is speed in units per second.) Tj
T*
ET
